2015年1月6日，克卜勒太空望遠鏡團隊宣布，確認系外行星已超過1000個；其中，最新發現的三個行星，[[克卜勒438b|克卜勒438b]]、[[克卜勒442b|克卜勒442b]]與[[克卜勒440b|克卜勒440b]]，分別處於它們各自太陽的[[適居帶|適居帶]]；在這三個新行星裏，有兩個可能是由岩石構成。<ref name="NASA-20150106">{{cite web |last1=Clavin |first1=Whitney |last2=Chou |first2=Felicia |last3=Johnson |first3=Michele |title=NASA's Kepler Marks 1,000th Exoplanet Discovery, Uncovers More Small Worlds in Habitable Zones |url=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?release=2015-003 |date=2015-01-06 |work=[[NASA|NASA]] |accessdate=2015-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150107031305/http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?release=2015-003 |archive-date=2015-01-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1月27日，英國[[伯明罕大學|伯明罕大學]]研究團隊發佈，從分析克卜勒太空望遠鏡數據，發現最古老的[[行星系|行星系]]，至少有5顆[[太陽系外行星|太陽系外行星]]圍繞著年齡為112億歲的[[恆星|恆星]][[克卜勒444|克卜勒444]]運轉。<ref name="ARX-20150126">{{cite journal |author=Campante, T.L. et al. |title=An ancient extrasolar system with five sub-Earth-size planets |url=http://arxiv.org/abs/1501.06227 |journal=Arxiv |doi=10.1088/0004-637X/799/2/170 |date=2015-01-26 |accessdate=2015-01-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151107084719/http://arxiv.org/abs/1501.06227 |archive-date=2015-11-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="AP-20150127">{{cite news |last=Dunn |first=Marcia |title=Astronomers find solar system more than double ours in age |url=http://apnews.excite.com/article/20150127/us-sci--old_solar_system-56b7594709.html |date=2015-01-27 |work=AP News |accessdate=2015-01-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150128131949/http://apnews.excite.com/article/20150127/us-sci--old_solar_system-56b7594709.html |archive-date=2015-01-28 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

7月23日，NASA宣布发现系外行星[[开普勒-452b|开普勒-452b]]，其距离地球1400光年。开普勒-452b围绕其恒星开普勒-452公转，距离主星位置适合液态水的存在。开普勒-452b的体积比地球大60%，有较大可能为岩石星球。它距离其主星恒星的距离，和地球和太阳之间的距离相似，这颗恒星本身距离地球430秒差距，在天鹅座。它比太阳稍亮，年龄较太阳大15亿年。<ref name="NASA-20150723">{{cite news |title=NASA’s Kepler Mission Discovers Bigger, Older Cousin to Earth |url=http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-kepler-mission-discovers-bigger-older-cousin-to-earth |date=2015-07-23 |work=NASA News |accessdate=2015-07-23 |archive-date=2015-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151007035447/http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-kepler-mission-discovers-bigger-older-cousin-to-earth/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

